<topic id='element_cancer_referral_to_treatment_period_start_date.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: CANCER REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>Format / Length</dt>
        <dd>an10 CCYY-MM-DD</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>

  <p>
 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_cancer_referral_to_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_activity_date">ACTIVITY DATE</xref>
, where the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_activity_date_type">ACTIVITY DATE TYPE</xref>
 is National Code 
    <i>
'
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_start_date">Start Date</xref>
'    </i>
 of the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_cancer_referral_to_treatment_period">Cancer Referral To Treatment Period</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="element"
            keyref="element_cancer_referral_to_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 will be one of the following:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
The 
                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_referral_request_received_date">REFERRAL REQUEST RECEIVED DATE</xref>
 of the 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service_request">SERVICE REQUEST</xref>
:        </p>
         </div>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <div>
                  <p>
to secondary care by a 
                        <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_medical_practitioner">GENERAL MEDICAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 or 
                        <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_dental_practitioner">GENERAL DENTAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 where the 
                        <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_priority_type">PRIORITY TYPE</xref>
 is National Code 
                        <i>'Two Week Wait'</i>
                     <b>*</b>
                  </p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li>
               <div>
                  <p>
to secondary care where the 
                        <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 was subsequently upgraded onto a 
                        <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                           keyref="business_definition_cancer_pathway">Cancer Pathway</xref>
. The 
                        <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_consultant_upgrade_date">CONSULTANT UPGRADE DATE</xref>
 will also be recorded, as this is the date used to calculate the start of the two month (62 day) waiting time target for 
                        <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 who have been upgraded to a 
                        <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                           keyref="business_definition_cancer_pathway">Cancer Pathway</xref>
                  </p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li>
               <div>
                  <p>
into secondary care when the 
                        <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 was referred urgently for 'breast symptoms', where the 
                        <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_priority_type">PRIORITY TYPE</xref>
 is National Code '
                        <i>Two Week Wait'</i>
                     <b>*</b>
                  </p>
               </div>
            </li>
            <li>
               <div>
                  <p>
to an Assessment Clinic following the identification of an abnormality by an NHS Cancer 
                        <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                           keyref="business_definition_screening_service">Screening Service</xref>
, where the 
                        <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_priority_type">PRIORITY TYPE</xref>
 is National Code 
                        <i>'Urgent'</i>
                     <b>*</b>
                  </p>
               </div>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
The 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_original_referral_request_received_date">ORIGINAL REFERRAL REQUEST RECEIVED DATE</xref>
 for the initial 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service_request">SERVICE REQUEST</xref>
 to secondary care by an NHS Cancer 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_screening_service">Screening Service</xref>
, where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_priority_type">PRIORITY TYPE</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>'Routine'</i>
, and where the 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 was subsequently upgraded onto a 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_cancer_pathway">Cancer Pathway</xref>
. The 
                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_consultant_upgrade_date">CONSULTANT UPGRADE DATE</xref>
 will also be recorded.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Notes:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <p>
* The start of the 
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_cancer_faster_diagnosis_pathway">Cancer Faster Diagnosis Pathway</xref>
 will be the 
            <xref outputclass="element"
                  keyref="element_cancer_referral_to_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER REFERRAL TO TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 for the items annotated.      </p>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
For a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service_request">SERVICE REQUEST</xref>
 received from the 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_definitions/choose_and_book.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Choose_and_Book</xref>
 system, the referral is received when the 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
's Unique Booking Reference Number (UBRN) is used to book the first 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment">Out-Patient Appointment</xref>
 slot (i.e. converted). See 
                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_referral_request_received_date">REFERRAL REQUEST RECEIVED DATE</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>


  </body>
